<li id="cite_note-55"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-55">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.arng.army.mil/history/Constitution/default.asp?ID=17">arng.army.mil</a></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-56"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-56">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://caselaw.lp.findlaw.com/scripts/getcase.pl?court=us&amp;vol=496&amp;invol=334">FindLaw for Legal Professionals – Case Law, Federal and State Resources, Forms, and Code</a></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-57"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-57">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Revised Code of Washington 38.04.030. Accessed via <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://apps.leg.wa.gov/RCW/default.aspx?cite=38.04.030">http://apps.leg.wa.gov/RCW/default.aspx?cite=38.04.030</a></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-58"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-58">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Mulloy, Darren. <i>American Extremism: History, Politics and the Militia Movement</i>, Routledge, 2004.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-59"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-59">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://constitution.org/mil/ustx_law.htm">http://constitution.org/mil/ustx_law.htm</a></span></li>
</ol>
</div>
